        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 4 at 7:45AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 745 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Salesville, or 8 miles southeast of Mountain Home, moving northeast
at 50 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vidette...                        Norfork Dam...
Diamond Bay...                    Gamaliel...
Ott...                            Lone Rock...
Gamaliel Landing...               Elizabeth...
Norfork Lake...                   Norfork...
Shipp...                          Briarcliff...
Salesville...                     Robinson Point Landing...
Viola...                          Henderson...
Gepp...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
